gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: This point data layer represents addresses for Clark County, WI in 2017. It is a feature class within the geodatabase Clark_Addresses_2017.gdb.[This data layer is an inventory for both rural and city/village addressing. The rural addressing system is based on the emergency response/rural address ordinance and managed through the Planning, Zoning & Land Information Office (PZ&LI). The rural address system runs on a N and W grid from the south east corner of the county. All unincorporated municipalities use the county rural address grid and are managed through PZ&LI. The address number for a location is determined based on the location of the driveway entrance to the named road. No address numbers are given from a private road. In cases such as that, unique address or a lot designation are assigned from the proximity to the driveway/road intersection.City/Village address number locations are entered by PZ&LI, however, the addressing in these locations is managed by each municipality and is not communicated directly with the county. Each municipality has a different origin location and directions for their address grid. Some cities and villages also extend into other counties and their locations are not included. The point locations are either directly in front the addressed structure or on the structure. City and village addresses in the database should not be considered as a complete inventory.]

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [The address layer marks the location of each known address number within Clark County. It is an inventory layer which is used by many departments, the community and businesses. Its main purpose is to serve the Planning and Zoning Dept and the Sheriffs Dept. It is served up to the public on the GIS site as well.]

gmd:supplementalInformation.gco:CharacterString: Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements. This data was submitted to the UW geospatial archive in 2017. Content may be considered current as of December 31, 2016. It was published to the UW geospatial archive as part of the Wisconsin Department of Administration Land Information Program annual collection of public data for the year 2017.

gmd:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: [Addresses are not associated with any topology. Due to the process of determining an address number, problems may be introduced later if the driveway intersection is moved.]
[Information has to come from property owners as to the need for a new address and where the address should be assigned from; this process lends itself to the possibility from external errors.]
Attribute information remains the same as given by the author of the data.

gmd:statement.gco:CharacterString: [The rural addressing system took place of the rural route system to promote the health, safety, comfort and general welfare of the public by establishing a method for physically locating properties, which is vital for providing emergency services as well as a convenience for other services that serve rural properties. The addressing system has been managed by several departments in the past but now resides with the Planning, Zoning and Land Information Office.]

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: [Typically an address request comes in indicating the location of the address. The Land Use Technician will go out to the field and do a visual verification that will sometimes include GPS collection. The data/information is then brought back and entered into the data set.]
